started about 4 years ago.

00:01:13.070 --> 00:01:15.130
He stopped by to pick
up some materials

00:01:15.130 --> 00:01:18.480
from the collection itself
and as he was going through,

00:01:18.480 --> 00:01:20.350
it was just, he was,

00:01:20.350 --> 00:01:22.960
it's obvious he was the
curator for the collection.

00:01:22.960 --> 00:01:25.660
He's picking up [inaudible]
and saying yes,

00:01:25.660 --> 00:01:30.740
this is the mantel piece that
belongs in the church and I,

00:01:30.740 --> 00:01:34.220
when I picked my job off
the floor, I was, you know,

00:01:34.220 --> 00:01:37.150
I was really thrilled that
somebody knew the collection

00:01:37.150 --> 00:01:42.190
so well and then at the same
time I was really disappointed

00:01:42.190 --> 00:01:45.920
that he was on a flight
back to Kentucky that night.

00:01:45.920 --> 00:01:53.410
And so, we've been working with
Paul to reclass the collection

00:01:53.410 --> 00:01:56.820
and this is why it's so
important that he's back here

00:01:56.820 --> 00:02:00.340
to help us, to help
us understand,

00:02:00.340 --> 00:02:04.360
to help curate this
collection, get it in front

00:02:04.360 --> 00:02:07.730
of the people who
need to see it.

00:02:07.730 --> 00:02:12.060
So, we have a keepsake that
you're holding right now.

00:02:12.060 --> 00:02:17.340
This is from the crooked crow
press, Chris Manson's press,

00:02:17.340 --> 00:02:21.260
and he's part of APHA,

00:02:21.260 --> 00:02:23.730
the American Print
History Association.

00:02:23.730 --> 00:02:26.990
And so, you may see that we have
2 dates on here; April 26th,

00:02:26.990 --> 00:02:30.110
of course today, and
April 27th, tomorrow.

00:02:30.110 --> 00:02:34.020
Tomorrow, Dr. Holbrook
will be giving a talk

00:02:34.020 --> 00:02:37.710
to APHA specifically and that's
why you'll see 2 dates on there.

00:02:37.710 --> 00:02:40.600
We're not missing anything
or that wasn't a typo.

00:02:40.600 --> 00:02:41.900
Though don't look too closely

00:02:41.900 --> 00:02:43.360
because we set some
of the [inaudible].

00:02:43.360 --> 00:02:46.460
This is a beautiful
piece despite the fact

00:02:46.460 --> 00:02:51.090
that [inaudible] helped
produce it, but not because of.

00:02:51.090 --> 00:02:56.480
So, Dr. Holbrook edited
a collection of letter

00:02:56.480 --> 00:02:59.400
between the [inaudible]
and Thomas [inaudible].

00:02:59.400 --> 00:03:01.890
Curated shows the victor's work

00:03:01.890 --> 00:03:06.320
and continues the [inaudible]
work and legacy as a printer

00:03:06.320 --> 00:03:08.630
and director of the
King Press Library

00:03:08.630 --> 00:03:11.880
at the university of Kentucky.

00:03:11.880 --> 00:03:16.510
Please help me to welcome
Dr. Paul Evans Holbrook.

00:03:16.510 --> 00:03:22.040
